==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: manual alphabet
<hw>manual alphabet</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An alphabet of signs made by
movement of the hands, used by the deaf; in it letters are represented
by finger positions. See <er>Dactylology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> finger alphabet.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>manual dexterity</ent>⟦br⟧
